That is where I bailed and I‚Äôll detail why; What I expected to see was a few actual quotes with at least ESTIMATED numbers
No extra steps
Give me some numbers and let me choose from there
Why estimated? Because they cannot possibly give you an exact quote because they do not ask all the variables specific to your situation
Which I hate to break it to you, is their hook to get you to fill out these questionnaires

EASY and QUICK, does that sound familiar and why you ended up here? So what I expected was a list with actual dollar numbers and a big disclaimer: ‚ÄúTHESE are estimated numbers please review this quote with your XXXX insurance agent at etc
etc
‚Äù I could have lived with that
I am going to speculate why I only received one quote and it was from a well established company (no not going to mention any company names, what was back in the day and may not be true today)
However that one company is the one we would happened to have referred them to for customers who did not meet stricter guidelines required for any of our other carriers
Again not a problem, we all have SPECIFIC things in our driving and life history that could have us down that path at some point
But that is the point
This site is probably best for those who just want someone else to narrow down who you should call based upon the basic questions they asked you (obviously)
HOWEVER You will still end up at the same point I was
maybe you will have 2 or 5 to call
Again you will still need to do the work, to speak with each individual carrier they recommend (answer more questions) to get a ACTUAL quote SPECIFIC to your situation
I would assume the more carrier ‚ÄúQUOTES‚Äù you receive then probably, those basic questions fit within the ‚Äúappetite‚Äù for ( read as a better risk ) for what that carrier is willing to quote on
By the way it is not as cut and dry as you think
My answers you would think would have garnered a few quote options
High credit score, no accidents, tickets, etc, driving many years, pleasure use, ‚Ä¶
all positive factors for most carriers would fight for ( read as LOWER RISK)
(by the way different states either allow or not some questions to be allowed or not in order to rate you
You can find that info on the web)
So bottom line there was something SPECIFIC to my answers that sent a red flag
I think I know which it was, and why only one carrier would quote
I know there are many more than one carrier that will write my business so if you get one quote I would urge you to looking and keep reading  below
You can call any insurance company directly
yes that is the reason so many of these types of sites have popped up

OR, INSTEAD work through a local BROKER that handles multiple insurance carriers ( ask them) and will know based upon a more detailed questionnaire which carriers they represent are willing to write YOUR SPECIFIC SITUATION!)

In other words you will probably save time because they will ask you all the specific questions and decide from a number of carriers they represent which top two or three will work with your SPECIFIC situation

You will get an exact quote Most brokers have a number of options to work with to handle multiple situations example: high asset value customers, to situations that are high risk and everything in between
By the way many of the positive reviews I read were about how happy they were with the customer service
I can‚Äôt say for sure
unless ZEBRA is also a broker for these companies they send to you as well, then more than likely you are either speaking with the carrier direct or a broker
Which means there are good service folks in multiple locations and you are NOT, speaking with Zebra folks
But I will let them clarify that if they decide to send me a happy reply
So let me summarize with this, no it is not fun or easy to shop for insurance
It is necessary
and the reasonI gave these guys a two star review first because they obviously fill a niche, who doesn‚Äôt want fast/easy
NOT complete/specific,
yes fast/easyAlso as I mentioned before I wasted my time because I saw no actual numbers, they said I would receive a quote, not an introduction into the ballroom for a dance
